<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.jakefitch.com/rta/RotationDetail.asp?ID=23">www.jakefitch.com/rta/Rot....asp?ID=23</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
If a guild is dedicated to keeping as many spawns down as they can, they prosper from FFA.  This is generally accepted as bad.  However it is a lot of work to keep every single spawn down.<br>
<br>
If a guild is dedicated to keeping the spawns that they are up for, which is most times a very attainable goal (unless you get random patch day of 10 spawn schedule), you still provide a steep barrier of entry for other guilds trying to expand their menu.  I know that my guild has had friction with other guilds, particularly Noble Blade leadership, over this exact problem.<br>
<br>
And then please add to this problem the dynamic of RTA politics and lawyering to protect rotation mobs of guilds who entered via &quot;gentlemen's agreements&quot; - when TL could blow 4+ AoW spawns trying to get on rotation, but once it is achievable by more than the big 3, and gets a real policy, a guild nowadays has to only attempt it on their statue turn and has to kill Idol unslowed and has to get a blessing from their pastor and grandmother.  What the fuck?  And the people who have the most influence in setting these barriers to entry are the people who got on the rotation under the &quot;gentlemen's agreement&quot;.  Great.<br>
<br>
I have been told that it is disrespectful to a rotation guild for them to log on to what they expected to be a normal rotation kill, zone in to XXX zone and realize they are in a race with another guild that nearly has a killing force in place.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Yes this not a polite approach.  I agree that it is usually preferable to carry on an attempt this way.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  But are you truly a villain for wanting to achieve a victory on a mob without the prior expressed written consent of a rotation guild at least one day in advance?  What the fuck ever happened to making it on your own anymore?  <br>
<br>
But no, we should ask the guilds on rotation when killing the mob to get on rotation would be convenient for THEM.  Sure you ask, and then you are gonna be met with &quot;well not tonight, we only have 2 mobs up to kill and that is one of them&quot;.  How many mobs do you need up to make it worthwhile to give one up?  Three?  Five?  Ten?  And you can come out and say that &quot;XXX mob isn't of much importance to us&quot; then why for instance does NB kill Arch Lich every spawn for the last 2 months?  <br>
<br>
Maybe you should be spending that time trying to get into tactics and  sol ro tower and not farming Arch Lich the day he spawns for 2 months...  <br>
<br>
I am sorry to NB for singling you out in my little rant - assured you are not alone in this.  But some our recent little frictions have made these examples the clearest in my mind, and the most detailed.  My point is, the rotation system does little to really prevent stifling of progression to other guilds, as long as you have guilds willing to farm the shit out of their turns.  If you are trying to get on a rotation and progress, you will eventually do it. Usually by the time that happens, at least for my guild, people are so fucking sick of hearing about the mob from countless failed planned attempts (sorry TL got here and they say all your cursed are belong to them, no G/E for you FK) that its an anticlimax.  It's no fun.  It is a drain to our morale to have to ask Noble Blade/Tindi`Losi/Blood of the Spider for permission to try a mob, because we are guranteed that for them to be willing to give it up it has passed beyond trivial for their guild.  At least we get respect from VoF/LoM/SotE most times because they share our vantage on the situation.  <br>
<br>
As one who respects the community, and order that rotations can provide, I can't help but still feel held down. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kitofvols>Kit of VoLS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 236<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(1/13/03 11:53:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=981.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.coolarchive.com/gifanimations/animals/kitty.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re</span><hr size=1> The horse is dead, leave it alone now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=baysarfk>BaysarFK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(1/13/03 11:53:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=981.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re</span><hr size=1> One correction - <br>
